author: Kate Kelland
title: Beware second waves of COVID-19 if lockdowns eased early: study
description: Extending school and work closures at the coronavirus' ground zero in China may delay a second wave of infections, researchers said on Thursday, urging the rest of the world to take note.
content:
LONDON (Reuters) - Extending school and work closures at the coronavirus’ ground zero in China may delay a second wave of infections, researchers said on Thursday, urging the rest of the world to take note.
